<div>
  <h3 style="font-size: 1.1rem; color: #259271; font-weight: 700">Problem Clarity</h3>
    <div style="font-size: 0.875rem; padding: 10px; text-align: justified">
      <p>Teams first capture enough clarity and understanding of the customer problems and problems for the company and what it means to solve them.  This enables an assessment of value and initial prioritization.  Only then do teams develop solution approaches and fully prioritize the work.</p>
      <p>The best investments solve customer problems in such a way that it directly contributes to strategic outcomes.</p>
      <p>An epic is usually a component of an initiative, split into multiple epics for iterative and incremental execution.  The sum of the epics equals the initiative. </p>
    </div>
</div>